# Web App Patterns

## App Router Structure

Route groups separate auth and main app flows:

- `(auth)/` — login, register (no main layout chrome)
- `(main)/` — authenticated app with Navbar + Sidebar

## Provider Hierarchy

Root layout wraps `ThemeProvider` → `AuthProvider`. Main layout adds `WorkspaceProvider`:

```
ThemeProvider → AuthProvider → WorkspaceProvider → Navbar + Sidebar + children
```

## Authentication

- JWT stored in `localStorage` as `orca_token`, user info as `orca_user` / `orca_user_name`
- `useAuth()` hook from `AuthProvider` exposes `hydrated`, `isLoggedIn`, `token`, `email`
- Main layout guards routes: redirects to `/login` when `hydrated && !isLoggedIn`

## Component Organization

- Shared components in `src/components/` (navbar, sidebar, providers, user-menu, theme-toggle)
- Route-scoped components in `_components/` directories under their route (e.g. `integration/_components/`)

## Tailwind & Theming

Use semantic token classes instead of raw colors:

```
bg-base, bg-surface, bg-primary, bg-primary/10
text-base-text, text-base-text-muted
border-base-border
```

Theme variables (light/dark + accent) are defined as CSS custom properties in `globals.css` and mapped in `tailwind.config.js`.

## Chat Integration

Uses Vercel AI SDK's `useChat` hook with `DefaultChatTransport` — not `@orca/sdk`. The transport configures the API endpoint and auth headers.
